<ce:para>An extended supply chain optimization model was developed for a large scale refinery industry. An MILP model was used to implement the optimization. The optimal scheduling can be obtained for the entire scheduling horizon by solving the model. In order to overcome the problem optimization horizon was chosen to be shorter than the scheduling horizon and a rolling horizon approach was introduced to determine scheduling for the entire scheduling horizon by repeatedly determining the schedule within the rolling optimization horizon. Using the rolling horizon approach, the decrease of objective value from the optimum was just 2%, and the CPU time was dramatically reduced.</ce:para>
